-- Toray Second-Quarter Profit Climbs 62% on Carbon Fiber Demand
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2013-11-07T06:10:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/toray-second-quarter-profit-climbs-62-on-carbon-fiber-demand.html
Toray Industries Inc. (3402) , the maker of
carbon fiber used in Boeing Co.’s 787 Dreamliner, said second-quarter profit rose 62 percent as demand for the material grew.  Net income rose to 16.1 billion yen ($163 million) in the
three months ended Sept. 30 from 9.9 billion yen a year ago, the
company said in a  statement  today. Sales rose 16 percent to 451
billion yen.  Operating profit at Toray’s carbon fiber business more than
doubled to 4.5 billion yen from 2 billion yen a year ago, while
sales rose 52 percent to 27.7 billion yen.  The environment and engineering business, which makes
water-treatment membranes, posted a fourfold gain in operating
income to 400 million yen during the period. Its sales rose 12
percent to 44.3 billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
